Jul 1 2009 	Extremely Basic Hotel-dont expect much	This hotel is located on a block full of hotels. We only like stayed at this hotel because all the other hotels nearby had no vacancies and we booked our trip very late. The positives: its in a good location, about a 5-10 minute walk to the Victoria Station and right near restaurants and pubs (as well as a bus stop right outside of the hotel). Its on a very quiet and pretty block and the staff is friendly. So about the rooms: they are very basic.. tiny tiny bathroom (our drain wasnt working so our little shower kept flooding), little to no space for your luggage, only 1 sheet separating you and the mattress, some of the towels looked dirty (like they had been used for the past 3 years). Also no elevator, so if your room is on the 5th floor prepare to lug your suitcases up 10 flights of stairs. They include breakfast but its basically toast and cereal. The price is reasonable, but compared to other hotels around the area it is a little expensive for what you get. If i had to do it over again I would definitely try to get another hotel in the area, as I am sure there is better.	
