Jul 7 2008 	Very very basic.	I stayed at the Lidos hotel for 2 nights in at the beginning of July 2008 with my family.The hotel is extremely basic, but in a good location, in the middle of Belgrave Road, a 7 min. walk from Victoria Station, so in that area there are all the facilities a tourist could needI booked a triple room by e-mail, the cost isn't so high for the location and the service, and the room is enough clean although the curtains are filthy and they give you only one towel per person.The breakfast that they serve in the morning is extremely poor: Bread, Jam and coffee. The remote control of the TV isn't working. The balcony is communicating with another room of the next hotel.There isn't Wi-fi connection, but this is not a problem because London is full of free hotspots.I would suggest this hotel if you don't want to spend a lot. Don't expect anything fancy.	
Apr 18 2008 	Not the best but great location	I stayed here with friends during the Christmas holidays. It looked like a quaint little place from the outside, but was certainly aged on the inside. There is no lift so we had to carry our suitcases to our basement level room. The room was small, not that big of a deal since it is not uncommon in Europe, however it was not very clean. The radiator worked well and we stayed warm despite the very chilly weather. The bathroom was awful. That was probably one of the worst I have seen. Very small and not clean. The trash was not changed regularly and the shower hose did not work. The breakfast was basic, but free so it was good enough. It included cork flakes, all of the tea or coffee and toast you could stand, and orange juice. The staff was good or bad depending on the time of day. The location was excellent. It was a short walk to Victoria station, and the locations for Grayline and Evan Evans tour companies and the bus stop was literally outside the hotel's front door so all of the city was easily accessible.	
