Oct 28 2006 	Small but clean and good location	I stayed at the Lidos with three friends. We arrived at about 11 pm. We were happy with the location of the hotel, it is only a 10 minute walk from Victoria station. We could get to the other side of the centre (tower bridge) in only half an hour from there.We booked a 4 bed room and it turned out that there were two double beds instead of 4 separate ones. This was disappointing, but we had kind of expected this as well. The room and the bathroom were very small, but reasonably clean. The breakfast was very simple, but there was plenty of it so we could make it to lunch easily. The staff were friendly and you could enter the hotel any time of the night. The hotel was very quiet.We would recommend the hotel to anyone looking for a quiet hotel with a good location for a low price, but don't expect much from the rooms.4 students from The Netherlands	
