Jul 31 2006 	Great staff room as expected	The room was really nothing fancy at all... a closet at the top of four flights of stairs. The private shower was a bonus. The bathrooms were not attractive, but they were clean. The best part about this hotel was that the staff were friendly and flexible. We arrived very early, our flight landed at 5:30 and we found ourselves at the front desk of Lidos by 7. They made cleaning our room a priority and had us checked in by 8! Don't be fooled by how easy the place is to find by the way the maps seem or the website promises, London streets are confusing and aren't logically ordered. Get good directions! We got a little lost and it was pouring so we got soaked. Everything in London cost a fortune, so the room was probably a good deal. The place was quiet. The breakfast was lacking, a simple corn flakes and toast, but the coffee had a kick. The place is well located for exploring all of central London. It was perfect for our short layover! We got to wander and see much of the prime London sights easily from Lidos. There is a bus stop RIGHT out front and the bus comes more frequently than every 10 minutes.	
Dec 6 2005	Tiny rooms but at least clean	I was travelling with my two adult children, so we booked a room for the three of us, which ended up being a double bed and a single jammed into a room which would have fitted the double adequately. However the sheets were clean and the floor reasonably clean, and there was a tv and coffee making facilities. There was barely room for our three bags and backpacks, so a little juggling was required. The 'bathroom' is typical of those in the UK that have been added on, sort of a plastic 'pod'. My son said it was like showering in a Jeffries Tube, for all the Star Trek fans out there! Breakfast was cereal, toast and coffee, better than any of those we had in Europe. Location is good, and other than the amount of space in the room, the hotel is quite acceptable.	
